{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0210a66d-2e9a-4b5a-9f9f-1e5aaed9eb1a","content":"Two key changes when moving to xUnit v3 with MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax changed\n\nThe VSTest `--filter` syntax (`FullyQualifiedName~X&Category=Y`) is **not** supported by MTP. Use the `--filter` flag with MTP's **treenode filter** syntax instead:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"/**/*IntegrationTests*[Category=Smoke]\"\n```\n\n- `/**/*IntegrationTests*` — matches any test whose path contains \"IntegrationTests\" (replaces `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests`)\n- `[Category=Smoke]` — matches the trait (replaces `Category=Smoke`)\n\n### 2. `--` separator for MTP args\n\nIf `dotnet test` doesn't forward the filter correctly, pass it explicitly to MTP:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- --filter \"/**/*IntegrationTests*[Category=Smoke]\"\n```\n\n### Quick reference\n\n| VSTest filter | MTP treenode filter |\n|---|---|\n| `FullyQualifiedName~Foo` | `/**/*Foo*` |\n| `Category=Smoke` | `[Category=Smoke]` |\n| `A&B` | combine in one glob: `/**/*Foo*[Category=Smoke]` |\n| `A\\|B` | use `/` separator or run two filters |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"19443335-8798-45f9-9e59-0e5f6f705578","outputTokens":337,"requestId":"480F:23D333:3183D4E:3628028:69FBE48B"},"id":"4b668421-c77a-4c67-b010-3919c38ee62a","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:02:16.761Z","parentId":"5c8bd72e-7ac4-4654-8d3d-723b369373c2"}
